definition.value: A D-galactose phosphate that consists of  D-galactopyranose having a single phospho substituent located at the 1-position. It is an intermediate obtained during the the galactose metabolism.
An anthraquinone in which the anthraquinone moiety is substituted by a single hydroxy group.
An anthraquinone substituted with one or more hydroxy groups.
A dihydroxyanthraquinone having the two hydroxy substituents at the 1- and 4-positions; formally derived from anthraquinone by replacement of two hydrogen atoms by hydroxy groups
A member of the class of  hydroxyanthraquinones carrying three hydroxy substituents.

3-Isopropylimino-3,5-dihydro-phenazine in which the hydrogen at position 5 is substituted substituted by a 4-chlorophenyl group, and that at position 2 is substituted by a (4-chlorophenyl)amino group. A dark red crystalline solid, clofazimine is an antimycobacterial and is one of the main drugs used for the treatment of  multi-bacillary leprosy. However, it can cause red/brown discolouration of the skin, so other treatments are often preferred in light-skinned patients.
A xylose phosphate that is D-xylose carrying a phosphate group at position 5.
An inositol having myo- configuration substituted at position 5 by a phosphate group.
A tetrahydroxyanthraquinone having the four hydroxy groups at the 1-, 2-, 5- and 8-positions.
A hexahydroxyanthraquinone that is anthracene-9,10-dione in which the six hydroxy substituents are located at positions 1, 2, 4, 5, 6 and 8. Used as as a hematoxylin substitute in H&E staining.
The ethyl ester of clofibric acid.
A  dihydroxyanthraquinone that is anthracene-9,10-dione substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 5.
An anthracenetriol having the three hydroxy substituents at the 1-, 2- and 10-positions.
A polyphenol that is anthracene carrying three hydroxy substituents.
A member of the class of  anthracenes in which the anthracene ring system is substituted by one or more hydroxy groups at unspecified positions.
An isoxazolidinone that is 1,2-oxazolidin-3-one substituted by a 2-chlorobenzyl group at position 2 and two methyl groups at position 4.
An anthracene compound derived by the substitution of -OH groups for hydrogen at C-1 and C-8, and with an oxo group at C-9.
A purine nucleoside monophosphate in which the sugar component is specified as arabinosyl.
The furanose form of D-fructose 1-phosphate.
A cycloheptatriene with unsaturation at positions 1, 3 and 5.
